This paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum weighted dominating induced matching in a graph, which is a problem related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of maximal independent sets, which is a topic related to graph theory and algorithms, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
